WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.880
Oliver Twist, chapter 1, the young woman.

00:07.880 --> 00:14.600
In a town in England, there was a building often found in most towns in England.

00:14.600 --> 00:17.720
It was a work house.

00:17.720 --> 00:21.040
Their Oliver Twist was born.

00:21.040 --> 00:26.400
The doctor and an old nurse looked at him.

00:26.400 --> 00:31.000
They were not sure if he would leave or die.

00:31.000 --> 00:37.040
However, at last he began to cry, like any other baby.

00:37.040 --> 00:44.280
Let me see my baby, said the young woman, who was Oliver's mother.

00:44.280 --> 00:52.880
She held the baby in her arms and kissed him, then she lay back and died.

00:52.880 --> 01:10.040
Oliver Twist, by Charles Dickens, chapter 1, the young woman.

01:10.040 --> 01:11.600
She was a beautiful girl.

01:11.600 --> 01:14.960
Where did she come from?

01:14.960 --> 01:17.200
Asked the doctor.

01:17.200 --> 01:21.600
She was brought here last night, answered the old woman.

01:21.600 --> 01:23.960
She was found in the street.

01:23.960 --> 01:29.840
She was very tired and her shoes were broken after walking for a long time.

01:29.840 --> 01:35.000
Nobody knows where she came from or where she was going to.

01:35.000 --> 01:38.760
The doctor lifted the left hand of the young woman.

01:38.760 --> 01:43.000
The old story, he said, shaking his head.

01:43.000 --> 01:46.480
No wedding ring, I see.

01:46.480 --> 01:50.000
The young woman must have run away from home.

01:50.000 --> 01:56.720
She could not tell her family that she was going to have a baby because she was not married.

01:56.720 --> 01:59.440
Oliver was now an orphan.

01:59.440 --> 02:07.720
He was crying loudly while the old nurse was raising him in the closet of the workhouse.

02:07.720 --> 02:15.640
Oliver Twist, by Charles Dickens, chapter 1, the workhouse.

02:15.640 --> 02:22.600
When Oliver Twist was ten-month-old, he was sent to a smaller workhouse.

02:22.600 --> 02:27.680
There were twenty or thirty other young orphans lying on the floor.

02:27.680 --> 02:33.000
They did not have many warm clothes or much food to eat.

02:33.000 --> 02:40.640
An old woman called Mrs. Mann was given seven-and-a-half pants each week to look after his child.

02:40.960 --> 02:47.240
Unfortunately, she took most of the money and spent very little on the children.

02:47.240 --> 02:52.040
As a result of this, Oliver Twist was thin and weak.

02:52.040 --> 02:56.440
He was also rather small.

02:56.440 --> 03:03.800
Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist, chapter 1, continue.

03:03.800 --> 03:11.040
On his ninth birthday, Oliver and two other boys told Mrs. Mann that they were hungry.

03:11.040 --> 03:14.680
She locked them in the cellar as punishment.

03:14.680 --> 03:22.280
While they were there, Mr. Bumble, the master of the workhouse, arrived to see Mrs. Mann.

03:22.280 --> 03:25.520
Goodness is that you, Mr. Bumble, sir.

03:25.520 --> 03:30.080
She said looked out of the window and saw him at the gate.

03:30.080 --> 03:34.000
How happy I am to see you, Mr. Bumble.

03:34.000 --> 03:41.120
Mr. Bumble was very fat and he walked slowly towards the front door of the house.

03:41.120 --> 03:43.520
Come in, sir, said Mrs. Mann.

03:43.520 --> 03:48.000
I told the dear children that you would visit them today.

03:48.000 --> 03:52.960
Well, well, Mrs. Mann, let's go inside, answered Mr. Bumble.

03:52.960 --> 03:59.920
I am here on business and I have something important to say.

03:59.920 --> 04:10.240
Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist, chapter 1, the workhouse, continue.

04:10.240 --> 04:17.680
Mrs. Mann took Mr. Bumble into his small kitchen and gave him a drink of gin from the bottle

04:17.680 --> 04:20.360
she kept in the cupboard.

04:20.360 --> 04:27.720
And now about business said Mr. Bumble, the child that we called Oliver Twist is nine

04:27.720 --> 04:34.160
years old today, was still not know where his mother came from, or who, his father

04:34.160 --> 04:37.440
is, said Mr. Bumble.

04:37.440 --> 04:42.360
Why is she called Oliver Twist, asked Mrs. Mann.

04:42.360 --> 04:45.080
I decided to call him that.

04:45.080 --> 04:48.800
We named the offerings in the alphabetical order.

04:48.800 --> 04:57.680
The one before him was S. This one was a T. So I named him Twist, replied Mr. Bumble.

04:58.680 --> 05:04.480
You are very clever, Mr. Bumble, said Mrs. Mann.

05:04.480 --> 05:10.040
Well, well, perhaps I am, replied Mr. Bumble.

05:10.040 --> 05:16.960
Oliver is too old to stay here now, so I am going to take him back to the large workhouse.

05:16.960 --> 05:20.200
Let me see him at once.

05:20.200 --> 05:25.400
Mrs. Mann took Oliver into the room to see Mrs. Bumble.

05:25.400 --> 05:28.120
Will you come with me, Oliver?

05:28.120 --> 05:34.400
Asked Mr. Bumble, Oliver was going to say that he would be happy to leave it when he

05:34.400 --> 05:39.640
saw Mrs. Mann looking at him angrily.

05:39.640 --> 05:43.240
Oliver tried to look sad.

05:43.240 --> 05:47.040
Mrs. Mann kissed him goodbye.

05:47.040 --> 05:52.480
Mr. Bumble took him to see the owners of the workhouse.

05:52.480 --> 05:55.160
Why, listen to me.

05:55.160 --> 05:58.040
Do you know that you are an orphan?

05:58.040 --> 06:02.840
Asked the fattest gentleman at the top of the table.

06:02.840 --> 06:05.000
What is that, sir?

06:05.000 --> 06:06.880
Asked Oliver.

06:06.880 --> 06:10.640
The boy is very stupid, said another gentleman.

06:10.640 --> 06:14.160
Do you know that you don't have parents?

06:14.160 --> 06:17.120
Said the first gentleman.

06:17.120 --> 06:19.920
You are here to learn how to work.

06:19.920 --> 06:21.840
You will begin to work.

06:21.840 --> 06:26.640
Tomorrow morning at six o'clock.

06:26.640 --> 06:31.360
Chance Dickens, Oliver Twist.

06:31.360 --> 06:36.320
Chapter 1, the workhouse continued.

06:36.320 --> 06:39.920
Life in the workhouse was very hard.

06:39.920 --> 06:46.000
The children had to work and were given three vowels of thin porridge every day.

06:46.000 --> 06:50.840
Oliver and the other boys were always very hungry.

06:50.840 --> 06:56.640
One day, a tall boy told the owners that if he was not given some more porridge, he

06:56.640 --> 07:00.640
would eat the boy's house left next to him.

07:00.640 --> 07:03.640
The other boys were frightened.

07:03.640 --> 07:10.600
They decided that one of them should ask the master for more after supper that evening.

07:10.600 --> 07:13.320
Oliver was chosen.

07:13.320 --> 07:18.960
In the evening, when the boy is finished eating, Oliver got up from the table.

07:19.040 --> 07:23.600
Please, sir, I want some more, he said.

07:23.600 --> 07:24.600
What?

07:24.600 --> 07:30.200
Said the master angrily and hit Oliver on the head with his pull.

07:30.200 --> 07:36.440
When Mr. Bumble heard that Oliver wanted more porridge, he said about the owner of the

07:36.440 --> 07:38.560
workhouse.

07:38.560 --> 07:43.000
That boy will be hand-walled day, said the owner.

07:43.000 --> 07:48.280
The next day, a notice, was put outside the door of the workhouse.

07:48.360 --> 07:54.760
He said that five pounds would be given to anyone who would take Oliver away.

07:54.760 --> 08:02.400
Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist, jumped to one, the chimney sweep.

08:02.400 --> 08:09.280
For the next week, Oliver was locked in a dark room.

08:09.280 --> 08:13.960
This was because he had asked for more porridge.

08:13.960 --> 08:20.680
At night, he put his hands over his eyes because he was afraid of the talk.

08:20.680 --> 08:27.280
Every evening, Oliver was taken to the larger hall and beaten while the other boys were

08:27.280 --> 08:29.720
watching it.

08:29.720 --> 08:36.440
One morning, a chimney sweep, called Mr. Gavild, was walking past the workhouse door.

08:36.440 --> 08:43.320
He saw the notice about Oliver and went to speak to the owners of the workhouse.

08:43.320 --> 08:49.400
And needed a boy to climb up inside chimneys and clean them.

08:49.400 --> 08:56.800
On the way to the magistrate, Mr. Bumble told Oliver to look very happy and tell the magistrate

08:56.800 --> 09:01.280
that he would like very much to be a chimney sweep.

09:01.280 --> 09:06.280
But Oliver said that he did not want to go with Mr. Gavild.

09:06.640 --> 09:14.760
Well, said Mr. Bumble, of all the orphans, I know you are the worst.

09:14.760 --> 09:20.840
Be quiet, said the magistrate, I will not sign these documents.

09:20.840 --> 09:26.320
The next day, a notice was put outside the door for the workhouse again.

09:26.320 --> 09:35.480
It said that five pounds would be given to anyone who would take Oliver away.

09:35.480 --> 09:39.720
Bogdan Nash, the turtle.

09:39.720 --> 09:46.600
The turtle lives twixt plated desks, which practically conceal its sex.

09:46.600 --> 09:54.160
I think it clever on the turtle, such a fix to be so frontal.

09:54.160 --> 09:59.280
Chapter 2 The Undertaker

09:59.280 --> 10:05.600
A few days later, Mr. Bumble was returning to the workhouse when he met a tall, thin

10:05.600 --> 10:13.280
man called Mr. Salvery, who was wearing a black suit because he was an undertaker.

10:13.280 --> 10:19.440
I have measured the two women who died last night, said Mr. Salvery.

10:19.440 --> 10:25.000
You will soon be a rich man, asked Mr. Bumble.

10:25.000 --> 10:31.360
The prices for the coffin are very small, and the wood is expensive, sir, answered Mr.

10:31.360 --> 10:32.360
Salvery.

10:32.360 --> 10:35.560
Do you know anyone who wants a boy?

10:35.560 --> 10:40.760
Asked Mr. Bumble, pointing to the notice about Oliver on the door.

10:40.760 --> 10:45.640
Yes, I wanted to ask you about that, said Mr. Salvery.

10:45.640 --> 10:49.480
I think I will take the boy to work for me.

10:49.480 --> 10:54.480
Last evening, Mr. Bumble took Oliver to Mr. Salvery's shop.

10:54.480 --> 11:00.320
Here is the boy I told you about Mr. Salvery, said Mr. Bumble.

11:00.320 --> 11:06.920
Mrs. Salvery, will you come here, my dear, said Mr. Salvery.

11:06.920 --> 11:13.040
Here is very small, but he will grow now a food and drink, said Mrs. Salvery.

11:13.040 --> 11:18.840
Mrs. Salvery taught Oliver to go downstairs into the kitchen, and then she gave the boy

11:18.840 --> 11:23.760
some of the co-pieces of meat left for the dog.

11:23.760 --> 11:30.160
Oliver ate the meat quickly and handily, while Mrs. Salvery was watching him.

11:30.160 --> 11:34.440
When he finished eating, she took him upstairs again.

11:34.440 --> 11:43.160
You will slip in here, with a conference, she said.

11:43.160 --> 11:46.760
Charles Dickens Oliver Twist

11:46.760 --> 11:53.880
Champed the tomb, nigh-claple.

11:53.880 --> 11:57.880
That night, Oliver was left to learn in the outer-taker's shop.

11:57.880 --> 12:04.880
Hey, looked around the shop, a conference toured in the middle of the room.

12:04.880 --> 12:08.880
When Oliver saw it, he got afraid.

12:08.880 --> 12:15.680
He was thinking about dead people and ghosts as he fell asleep.

12:15.680 --> 12:22.280
In the morning, Oliver heard someone kicking loudly at the front door of the shop.

12:22.280 --> 12:27.280
Oliver slowly opened the door, and saw an old boy sitting on a wall.

12:27.280 --> 12:30.360
He was eating some bread and butter.

12:30.360 --> 12:33.760
Do you want to buy a conference, sir?

12:33.760 --> 12:34.760
Asked Oliver.

12:34.760 --> 12:39.040
Don't you know who I am?

12:39.040 --> 12:40.880
Said the old boy.

12:40.960 --> 12:47.440
I am Mr. Nigh-Claple, and you work under me.

12:47.440 --> 12:53.120
Nigh- when downstairs to speak to Charles, he was not an orphan.

12:53.120 --> 12:59.680
His family was poor, but he lived at home with his parents.

12:59.680 --> 13:06.720
One evening Mr. Salvery said to his wife that Oliver looks sad and would be good at children's

13:06.720 --> 13:07.720
funerals.

13:08.720 --> 13:12.360
Well, Oliver, how did you like it?

13:12.360 --> 13:14.320
Not very much, sir.

13:14.320 --> 13:15.320
Replied Oliver.

13:15.320 --> 13:20.760
You'll get used to it in time, Oliver said Mr. Salvery.

13:20.760 --> 13:26.200
One day, Oliver and Nigh-Claple were alone in the kitchen.

13:26.200 --> 13:34.280
Nigh- was jealous of Oliver because Mr. Salvery let Oliver help him and if you know, he began

13:34.280 --> 13:37.240
to make fun of Oliver.

13:37.240 --> 13:43.920
You know your mother was a bad woman, said Nigh- and it's a good thing, she did, because

13:43.920 --> 13:47.120
now she would be in prison.

13:47.120 --> 13:56.240
Oliver jumped up, grabbed Nigh- by throat, and knocked him to the ground.

13:56.240 --> 14:05.080
Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist, chapter two, Nigh-Claple, continue.

14:05.080 --> 14:06.080
Help!

14:06.080 --> 14:07.080
Charlotte!

14:07.080 --> 14:08.080
Mrs. Salvery!

14:08.080 --> 14:09.080
Help!

14:09.080 --> 14:11.080
He's murdering me!

14:11.080 --> 14:12.080
Shouted Nigh.

14:12.080 --> 14:18.320
Charlotte screamed and Mrs. Salvery ran into the kitchen.

14:18.320 --> 14:22.680
They both grabbed Oliver and hit him several times.

14:22.680 --> 14:27.560
Nigh got up from the ground and began to hit Oliver too.

14:27.560 --> 14:30.680
Then they took him to the cellar.

14:30.680 --> 14:37.240
When Oliver was safe to lock up, Mrs. Salvery sat down on a chair and began to cry.

14:37.240 --> 14:41.800
Well, lucky that he didn't murder us, said Mrs. Salvery.

14:41.800 --> 14:45.560
Yes, we are very happy to bear life, said Charlotte.

14:45.560 --> 14:51.640
I hope the master will not take it any more of these workhouse boys that are born to be

14:51.640 --> 14:54.800
murderer and robbers.

14:54.800 --> 14:58.840
He nearly murdered Parnoy.

14:58.840 --> 15:03.720
What shall we do with him now, asked Mr. Salvery?

15:03.720 --> 15:10.160
I know, run to Mr. Bumble Nigh and tell him to come here immediately.

15:10.160 --> 15:16.440
Mr. Bumble immediately went with Nigh to the undertaker's shop.

15:16.440 --> 15:23.240
Then Mr. Salvery unlocked the cellar door and pulled Oliver out.

15:23.240 --> 15:25.160
Oliver was not afraid.

15:25.160 --> 15:29.720
They looked at Nigh and said, he called my mother names.

15:29.720 --> 15:32.320
So what?

15:32.320 --> 15:34.240
Said Mr. Salvery.

15:34.240 --> 15:35.720
She dissolved.

15:35.720 --> 15:37.120
What he said.

15:37.120 --> 15:39.400
No, she didn't.

15:39.400 --> 15:42.480
It's a lie, said Oliver.

15:42.480 --> 15:46.120
At this Mrs. Salvery began to cry.

15:46.120 --> 15:52.240
Mr. Salvery beat Oliver and Mr. Bumble hit Oliver with his tick.

15:52.240 --> 15:55.480
Then they locked him in the room with the conference.

15:55.480 --> 16:01.040
As Oliver said there, he was thinking about running away.

16:01.040 --> 16:04.560
He decided to try to leave the sobber's shop.

16:04.560 --> 16:11.320
He slowly got up from the floor, carefully unlocked the door and opened it.

16:11.320 --> 16:14.760
There was the cold and dark night outside.

16:14.760 --> 16:17.160
Oliver was afraid of the tuck.

16:17.160 --> 16:20.600
He decided to wait until morning came.

16:20.600 --> 16:29.480
Then it was light, Oliver got up, opened the door and went outside into the street.

16:29.480 --> 16:38.800
Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist, Chapter 3 to London, Oliver didn't know where to go.

16:38.800 --> 16:44.120
Then he remembered the way Mr. Bumble had brought him to the sobber's shop from the

16:44.120 --> 16:45.920
workhouse.

16:45.920 --> 16:50.360
It was very early in the morning, so nobody saw him.

16:50.360 --> 16:55.640
Then he walked on until he came to the small workhouse for young boys.

16:55.640 --> 16:58.720
Oliver stopped and looked into the garden.

16:58.720 --> 17:02.440
He saw a friend there, working in the garden.

17:02.440 --> 17:08.840
Hello, Dick, Oliver said quietly, is anyone awake?

17:08.840 --> 17:11.680
Only me replied the young boy.

17:11.680 --> 17:18.520
You mustn't say that you saw me, Dick, said Oliver, I'm running away.

17:18.520 --> 17:24.360
I'm very happy to see you, but don't stop, don't stop, said Dick.

17:24.360 --> 17:29.840
I'll say goodbye to you, Dick, but I'll come back here again one day.

17:29.840 --> 17:33.000
I know I will, said Oliver.

17:33.000 --> 17:38.960
I hope so, replied Dick, goodbye and God bless you.

17:38.960 --> 17:44.440
There were the first kind words Oliver had in his life.

17:44.520 --> 17:52.440
Oliver ran and walked as far as he could from the town until he was nearly five miles away.

17:52.440 --> 17:58.040
Then he sat down to rest and saw the sign by the side of the road.

17:58.040 --> 18:02.520
The words of the sign were written in large letters.

18:02.520 --> 18:08.680
They said, London, seventy miles.

18:08.680 --> 18:15.640
They continued walking for seven days, and kind people gave him some bread and water.

18:15.640 --> 18:21.560
Eventually he came to Barnet, a small town not far from London.

18:21.560 --> 18:26.640
It was very early in the morning, and there was nobody in the street.

18:26.640 --> 18:31.200
Suddenly Oliver's boy were in strange clothes.

18:31.200 --> 18:34.760
He had a long coat and a large hat.

18:34.760 --> 18:38.840
He was shot, but he looked like a little man.

18:38.840 --> 18:42.400
The boy came over and spoke to Oliver.

18:42.400 --> 18:43.400
Hello?

18:43.400 --> 18:44.880
What's wrong with you?

18:44.880 --> 18:45.880
He asked.

18:45.880 --> 18:52.320
He looked very hungry, come with me, and I'll give you something to eat.

18:52.320 --> 18:58.640
My name is Jack Dawkins, but my friends call me the Artful Dodger.

18:58.720 --> 19:06.000
Then Dodger took Oliver to an ugly and dirty part of the city.

19:06.000 --> 19:11.040
He opened the door of the house and pulled Oliver inside.

19:11.040 --> 19:14.000
The inside of the room was very dirty.

19:14.000 --> 19:21.240
There was a table in the middle of the room with a candle on it, and all the men were standing near the fire.

19:21.240 --> 19:24.760
He was cooking some sausages in a pan.

19:24.760 --> 19:32.640
The old man had long red hair, and he was very dirty, old coat.

19:32.640 --> 19:36.800
There were some silk handkerchiefs on the line beside him.

19:36.800 --> 19:40.440
Four or five bars were sitting at the table.

19:40.440 --> 19:43.880
They were smoking pups and drinking gin.

19:43.880 --> 19:52.360
This is my friend Oliver Twist, said Dodger after he had whipped something to the old man.

19:52.360 --> 19:59.000
The old man smiled at Oliver, shook his hand, and said that his name was Foggin.

19:59.000 --> 20:03.320
They are very happy to see Oliver, said Foggin.

20:03.320 --> 20:06.280
Then they all sat down to eat.

20:06.280 --> 20:14.560
Foggin gave Oliver drink of gin, and soon he felt very tight.

20:14.560 --> 20:23.600
Just Dickens, Oliver Twist, Chapter 3, Foggin's Gamm.

20:23.600 --> 20:30.480
The next morning, when Oliver woke up, he saw Foggin making some coffee by the fire.

20:30.480 --> 20:34.320
The old man did not see that Oliver was awake.

20:34.320 --> 20:40.000
He opened a secret hole in the floor and took out a small box.

20:40.000 --> 20:44.400
He took out a good watch from the box and said,

20:44.400 --> 20:51.280
clever dogs, they didn't tell the police about me, good man, good man.

20:51.280 --> 20:59.680
Then he took six more watches and submarines and other pieces of jewelry from the box.

20:59.680 --> 21:02.960
Suddenly he saw Oliver watching him.

21:02.960 --> 21:09.280
Foggin looked at Oliver for a few seconds and spoke in a kind voice.

21:09.280 --> 21:12.160
Did you see any of these pretty things?

21:12.160 --> 21:13.440
Said Foggin.

21:13.440 --> 21:15.360
They are mine, Oliver.

21:15.360 --> 21:19.120
They all I have when I am old.

21:19.120 --> 21:25.680
Oliver thought it was a little strange that man with so many beautiful watches lived in

21:25.680 --> 21:28.480
a dirty old house.

21:28.480 --> 21:34.560
Oliver got up and went to the corner of the room to wash his face.

21:34.640 --> 21:38.720
When he turned round, the box was not on the table anymore.

21:39.680 --> 21:44.160
Just then the dodger returned to the house with one of the other boys.

21:44.960 --> 21:47.440
The other boy was called Charlie Bates.

21:48.080 --> 21:55.280
The dodger took some bread and some meat from inside his hat and they all sat down for breakfast.

21:56.240 --> 21:57.680
One did you get?

21:57.680 --> 21:59.680
Said Foggin to Dodger and Charlie.

22:01.120 --> 22:06.080
Four hangagers said Charlie and gave them to Foggin.

22:07.440 --> 22:08.160
Very good.

22:08.880 --> 22:13.440
Teacher Oliver, how to pick out the labels with a needle, said Foggin.

22:14.480 --> 22:20.000
After breakfast, Charlie and Dodger played a very strange game with Foggin.

22:20.960 --> 22:29.120
The old man put on a coat, then he put a watch, a wallet, and some hangagers into his pockets.

22:30.240 --> 22:33.280
Next, he walked up and down the room.

22:34.080 --> 22:36.960
Sometimes he stopped near the fire or the door.

22:37.840 --> 22:41.200
He looked like another man shopping in the street.

22:42.560 --> 22:47.520
The dodger and Charlie followed him while he walked up and down the room.

22:48.480 --> 22:53.120
Suddenly, the dodgers took on the old man's feet and Charlie pushed him.

22:54.160 --> 22:59.520
While they did this, the two boys quickly took all the things from Foggin's pockets.

23:00.320 --> 23:02.880
This game was played several times.

23:02.880 --> 23:07.840
If Foggin knew that one of the boys' hands was in his pocket,

23:07.840 --> 23:11.600
he would stop again and they would start again.

23:12.480 --> 23:14.720
Oliver enjoyed watching the game very much.

23:15.680 --> 23:20.880
When the boys went to see any workout, Foggin said to Oliver,

23:21.760 --> 23:26.400
Can you take this handkerchief from my pocket without my feeling it?

23:27.840 --> 23:29.920
Oliver did, as Foggin asked.

23:30.880 --> 23:33.200
Your dear reclaver Oliver said, Foggin.

23:33.920 --> 23:38.880
If you learn as quickly as this, you'll soon be a great man.

23:40.240 --> 23:42.640
Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist.

23:43.600 --> 23:44.640
Chapter 4

